          "fetus_content_w1":
              "That is right! Week 1 starts with the very first day of your last menstrual period. Since it is hard for your doctor to figure that exact day when you ovulated, or when the sperm and the egg have met in your fallopian tube, he will count your gestational weeks starting from the first day of your last menstrual period. Ovulation will take place roughly two weeks afterwards, when the egg released by your ovary will travel to your fallopian tube, and wait to be fertilized by the sperm. When this happens, you are already two weeks into pregnancy!",
